title: Grateful Dead Live at Nassau Coliseum on 1994-03-28
lineage: Dat > Panasonic SV-3700 > Tascam DA-3000 > wav 16/48; Edited & Mastered in Audacity by Joe Noel: wav 16/48 > flac 16/48; Checksum & tags created in xACT
description:
Set 1

Let The Good Times Roll, Bertha, Greatest Story Ever Told, West L.A. Fadeaway, When I Paint My Masterpiece, It Must Have Been The Roses, Beat It On Down The Line, Peggy-O, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Rain, Victim Or The Crime-> Box Of Rain, He's Gone-> That Would Be Something-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Drums-> Space-> All Along the Watchtower-> Days Between-> Turn on Your Lovelight, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: a little better Able to listen for a little while with the higher levels, but only through Bertha, too noisy, it breaks up at higher volume needed to hear it.

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Not the best AUD quality at all. I'm not sure who wrote "a good show & an even better recording" in the notes (Charlie?), but it is still an enjoyable listen. 

Fairly good first set with a West LA, Roses, and Peggy-O from Jerry. Bobby has been consistently great throughout this run, and his first set tunes are all worth a listen. Masterpiece is always nice. 

My favorite Beatles cover, Rain, shines as a second set opener, and Box of Rain is nice, but the song selection for set two is not to my liking. Decent performances though. Special mention for epic Vince singing. That Would Be Something would be a great song, but it needs a bridge.
